Description:
Unify AI Tech LLC is seeking a highly skilled and motivated Data Scientist for its Boston, MA location. The Data Scientist is pivotal in the development and implementation of our AI-driven reasoning system, focusing on areas such as entity recognition, information retrieval, semantic data representations, and graph-based search optimizations. The Data Scientist will be responsible for performing the following job duties:


Collaborate with AI Scientists, ML Engineers, and Software Engineers to develop, optimize, and bring into production our generative AI powered CX automation platform;
Build and evaluate machine learning models suited to deeply embedded CX automation use cases, like chatbots, and contact center QA;
Play a key role in the data transformation process for custom model training, including programmatic and analytics driven data quality enrichment, feature engineering, and data integration tailored to the requirements of tasks like embedded vector search, generative QnA in agentic flows, and domain specific intent recognition;
Assist in the analysis and interpretation of complex data to derive actionable insights and support data driven business critical design choices;
Monitor and evaluate model performance pre and post deployment; and
Perform regular model maintenance and updates as part of a CI/CD pipeline, taking into account the unique challenges posed by our targeted problem space.


Required

Must have a Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Data Analytics, or closely related field and 3 years of related data science experience. Required experience must include 3 years of experience in the following specific skills:


Python for programming in our stack;
Pandas for data manipulation;
Numpy for numerical analysis;
Scikit-learn for machine learning algorithms and evaluation metrics;
Matplotlib, Seaborn, and Tableau for data visualization;
NLP Techniques such as Transformer models and large language models (LLMs) for NLP tasks such as entity recognition, QnA, and sentiment analysis; and
Machine Learning Frameworks such as TensorFlow or PyTorch for developing and training machine learning models;


Required experience must also include at least 2 years of experience in the following specific skills:


Plotly and Bokeh for interactive visualizations; and
ggplot for data visualization.


This position can work remotely 2-3 days a week, but is required to work in office at least 1-2 days per week. Wage range: $145,000-$215,000.
